<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-31T18:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-14T19:00:00-05:00" n="334" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                    <head>Chamber of Commerce of Dewsbury</head>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>Dewsbury</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1865-07-31T23:59:59+00:00" notBefore="1865-04-15T00:00:00+00:00">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="italic">Resolution passed by the Chamber of Commerce,
                            Dewsbury</hi>.</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="italic">Resolved</hi>, That this council expresses its utter
                        abhorrence and detestation of the foul crime which has deprived a kindred
                        nation of its President at such a momentous crisis in its history; and that
                        such expression of the indignation of the council, together with its
                        sympathy, be conveyed to the American consul at Leeds.</p>
                    <p>The <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consul</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Leeds</hi>.</p>
                </div>
